traffic_visible_response: The May Fourth Movement, which erupted on May 4th, 1919, stood as a seminal event in Chinese history, marking a national campaign against foreign imperialism [[1]]. It was directed toward national independence, emancipation of the individual, and rebuilding society and culture [[4]]. One of the slogans of the movement was a call for 'Mr. Democracy' and 'Mr. Science,' meaning for democracy and science [[2]]. The movement also represented an ambitious effort to achieve national independence, personal freedom, and the reconstruction of Chinese society and culture [[5]]. Additionally, it was a patriotic campaign launched by Chinese youth against imperialism and feudalism [[7]].
